<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-10-31T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-10-31T03:00:00-05:00" n="150" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d150">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">867n.01/363: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cobb</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Jerusalem</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-10-31T10:00:00+02:00"><hi rend="italic">October 31,
                                        1923—10 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 7
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Officially informed Palestine mandate definitely effective September
                            29th. Increasing difficulties with civil courts. Protested to local
                            government who have again requested instructions from London.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>